The paper proposes a novel approach using recurrent neural networks for sequence embedding and similarity search. This falls under the domain of machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.LG, cs.AI). The use of deep learning models for sequence analysis and classification is a common theme in computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL), which are also likely sub-categories. Finally, the paper mentions the use of approximate nearest neighbor algorithms, which is a common technique in the field of neural networks (cs.NE).
